25\%=\frac{25}{100}=.25
x
\frac{100}{25}=4
.25=\frac{25}{100}=\frac{1}{4}
.25
 \text{percent}\times \text{what number} = \text{the given number} 
 \frac{25}{100}\times x = 150 \qquad \text{OR} \qquad .25\times x=150 
 \frac{100}{25}\times\frac{25}{100}\times x = 150\times\frac{100}{25} \Rightarrow x=600 
 \frac{1}{.25}\times .25\times x = 150\times \frac{1}{.25} \Rightarrow x=600 
 \frac{1}{.25}=\frac{1}{\frac{1}{4}}=4 
